<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[264,1323,283,790]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,599,283,309]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis and remarks</emphasis>
. There were only a few specimens available to me for examination. For features such as the morphometric ratios, the shape of the cerci and the colour of the tibiae, 
<taxonomicName box="[427,560,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Pales" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exsulans">
<emphasis box="[427,560,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. exsulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
falls well within the range of variability of 
<taxonomicName box="[1096,1207,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Pales" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pavida">
<emphasis box="[1096,1207,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. pavida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only noticeable difference being the ground colour of the thorax (except scutellum) and abdomen which are entirely black, without blue reflections. On the basis of these findings, it seems that no sound morphological evidence separating the two species exists so, accordingly, 
<taxonomicName box="[340,473,524,549]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Pales" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exsulans">
<emphasis box="[340,473,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. exsulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably synonymous with 
<taxonomicName box="[850,961,524,549]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Pales" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pavida">
<emphasis box="[850,961,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. pavida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, because of the geographic isolation of 
<taxonomicName box="[540,670,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Pales" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exsulans">
<emphasis box="[540,670,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. exsulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and lack of information on its biology and reproductive isolation, it is more appropriate not to propose a formal synonymy of the two names at this time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
